<AbstractNarration>This proposal consists of two tasks&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Decision making under the suspicion of deception&lt;br/&gt;Decision making under social and hierarchical pressure&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;As stated in the proposal, cognitive scientists and social psychologists have studied decision making under uncertainty a great deal. However there are few studies analyzing faulty information. The project will attempt to study such situations by creating potential deceptions and studying how humans react and make decisions. &lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
